<br>
Unless things are going on behind the scenes that I nobody knows about I'm not to hopeful about skald changes.  So DA range is increased but it's not really improved.  No increase in dps no stacking with other skalds dmg add.  Your group still won't notice weather you put it on or not.  Shout changes sound promising.  I hope they lower the recast timer which I think they'll do and hopefully they'll fix the resist rates on them.  It still leaves a the number 1 problem imo and that's skalds survivability.  I don't think our damage output (which for most is pretty low considering we use a slow 2h wep)  and our support/utility justify our almost 0 defense. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jikkle01>Jikkle01</A> at: 9/5/03 11:44 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kjeld>Kjeld</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Fervent</span><br>  Posts: 344<br> <font color=#ff0000>(9/7/03 4:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=689.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> bleh</span><hr size=1> Hmm this is a lackluster answer at best. The report was even more carefully worded, but the guy seems to miss the point entirely.<br>
<br>
This sums up everything : the original design document of the skald has been long lost, and no one has a clue about what to do with the class. Sorry to be harsh but RvR is brutal. RvR is 3l33t. RvR is all about maxxed out, spellcrafted characters. RvR is about competing with flavor of the month classes or group compositions. Watered down defense and poopy poor offense works when soloing werewolves, or toying around in the battlegrounds. The RvR is balanced around melee classes spellcrafted to the gills with tons of hps and good defense skill sets soaking the damage of real melee classes with maximized damage outputs. If you can't compete with the big boys  &quot;to be in the thick of battle rather then orbiting on the outskirts&quot; is pointless. It's like removing all range from mages, giving them a zero range single target DD ans say &quot;go, go to the thick of the battle&quot;. It doesn't make them melee classes.<br>
<br>
The answer about the parry skill tells how much he misses the point. He isn't conviced that removing weapon skill points to pump up parry won't help the skald ? Irrelevant. However you balance weapon and parry, you still only have 1.5 spec, poor evade, no shield, poor hps. Even the purely offensive hybrids have at least the luxury to put 2.0 spec points.<br>
<br>
The most ironic thing about the report is that they are upping damage add range ... and maybe they could be convinced to put shout range to 1500 (will be the best thing for skalds in ages if we conviced them to do that),as they didn't close the door on shout reevaluation. Ironically, it will just allow skalds more breathing room to actively avoid melees they are not fit for. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xerofury>xerofury</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#ff0000>(9/17/03 10:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=689.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: bleh</span><hr size=1> I think the reason mythic doesnt know what to do with the Skald class is because the Skald class is so similuar to the Thane class.<br>
